  section#faq
    .container
      .row
        .col-md-12
          h1 FAQ
      .row
        .col-md-4
          h3 What is a Hackathon?
          p Hackathons are where thoughts become things, collaborating, coding and creating literally anything. Attendees work in teams of up to four people to create a hack, web, app, hardware or anything.
        .col-md-4
          h3 When is OxfordHack?
          p Registration for OxfordHack will open at 6:00PM and start at 9:30PM Friday April 19st until the morning of the 21st.
        .col-md-4
          h3 What if I have another question?
          p Tweet us at 
            a(href='http://twitter.com/hackupc') SOCIAL
            |  or drop us a line at 
            a(href='mailto:info@hackupc.com') EMAIL
      .row
        .col-md-4
          h3 Do you have a code of conduct?
          a(href='http://static.mlh.io/docs/mlh-code-of-conduct.pdf') Yes
          | . tl;dr: Be excellent to each other.
        .col-md-4
          h3 What if I don't have a team?
          p No need to worry! Part of the fun of a hackathon is meeting new people. We will have time at the beginning of the event for everyone to meet and form teams.
        .col-md-4
          h3 What can I build?
          p Web, mobile, hardware, anything is on the table. Projects will be judged based on creativity, technical difficulty, polish and usefulness by a panel of industry judges.
      .row
        .col-md-4
          h3 Where is it being held?
          p Oxford
        .col-md-4
          h3 Who can attend?
          p Students from universities and high schools from all around the world.
        .col-md-4
          h3 How much does it cost?
          p OxfordHack is free for all accepted hackers. We provide you WiFi, meals, swag, and workspace. We also have a limited number of travel scholarships - up to 50€ if you're traveling from outside of Oxford.
      .row
        .col-md-4
          h3 What should I bring?
          p All attendees must bring a valid ID for admission. Other common checklist items include: laptops, sleeping bags, chargers and toiletries. If you want to shower, bring a towel!
        .col-md-4
          h3 How big can teams be?
          p Teams of up to four are welcome. You can also hack solo if you want!
